    <section id="design">
      <h2>Platform &amp; Build Quality</h2>
      <p>SEO Writing AI is a cloud-hosted SaaS platform with a web-based dashboard. All content generation and management happens through the browser — there is no desktop app. A Shopify app and a WordPress plugin are available for integration.</p>

      <h3>Technology Architecture</h3>
      <p>The platform connects to multiple LLM providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, Meta, DeepSeek, Groq) via their APIs and uses proprietary AI technology for specific tasks including SERP analysis, content scoring, and the Amazon affiliate builder. Articles can be up to 5,000 words per generation. The WordPress MCP (Model Context Protocol) server enables direct publishing without additional plugins.</p>

      <h3>Data Flow</h3>
      <p>The core workflow follows a simple pipeline: user enters a keyword → AI fetches SERP competitor data → generates article with heading structure, keyword placement, and images → optional auto-publish to WordPress or Shopify. This keyword-to-published-article flow in a single session is a meaningful differentiator for content creators who value speed over manual optimisation.</p>

      <h3>Supported AI Models</h3>
      <p>Based on the platform's FAQ and documentation, SEO Writing AI works with models from OpenAI, Anthropic, Meta, DeepSeek, and Groq. The platform also has proprietary AI technology for specific tasks such as the humanizer and the Amazon product builder.</p>

      <h3>Security &amp; Compliance</h3>
      <p>A privacy policy is published at seowriting.ai/privacy-policy. Beyond standard web-application security (HTTPS, password-protected accounts), no specific certifications (SOC 2, GDPR compliance statements) were prominently featured in the reviewed documentation. The platform stores user-generated content and API keys for connected services.</p>

      <h3>Visual Appeal &amp; Trust Signals</h3>
      <p>The homepage presents a clean, modern design with prominent trust signals: WordPress Plugin Directory ratings (4.9), G2 ratings (4.6), and Capterra ratings (4.8) are displayed in the hero section alongside the "50,000+ businesses, bloggers, and agencies worldwide" claim. Six customer testimonials with photos are displayed. The design is functional and straightforward — it prioritises information density over visual flourish.</p>
    </section>

