      <h3>Key Features</h3>

      <h4>One-Click SEO Article Generation</h4>
      <p>The core feature. Enter a keyword, and the AI generates a complete long-form article optimised for search rankings. The platform auto-analyses SERP competitors to inform content structure, keyword density, and heading hierarchy. Articles can be up to 5,000 words. This is the feature that most directly differentiates SEO Writing AI from general AI writers — the SEO optimisation is built into the generation step, not applied as a post-processing layer.</p>

      <h4>Bulk Article Generation</h4>
      <p>Supports generating up to 100 articles in a single batch from a keyword list. Articles can be auto-scheduled on WordPress with staggered publishing times. The vendor claims "1,000+ articles in hours" using this feature. For content marketers running multiple sites or agencies producing client content, this is potentially the platform's highest-value capability — if the batch quality holds up across all 100 outputs.</p>

      <h4>WordPress MCP Integration</h4>
      <p>The WordPress MCP server enables direct auto-publishing of generated articles. Articles can be published immediately or scheduled. The system auto-generates meta titles, meta descriptions, and image alt tags. The WordPress plugin holds a 4.9/5 rating from 117 reviews, suggesting reliable performance in the field — though plugin ratings should be interpreted cautiously as they often reflect a self-selected user base.</p>

      <h4>NLP SEO Checker &amp; Content Score</h4>
      <p>Built-in content scoring evaluates keyword placement and density, readability and content depth, and technical SEO elements (headings, meta tags, alt text). The system provides actionable recommendations to reach 100% optimisation. This gives writers a concrete target — "score of X out of 100" — rather than vague SEO guidance.</p>

      <h4>Amazon Affiliate Article Builder</h4>
      <p>A specialised tool for affiliate marketers. Users enter product URLs and ASINs, and the AI generates product descriptions, pros/cons lists, specifications, and reviews. This is a unique feature not commonly found in competing AI writing tools. For affiliate site operators who produce product roundups and reviews, this directly addresses a repetitive, high-volume content task.</p>

      <h4>AI Text Humanizer</h4>
      <p>Post-generation tool that removes AI-detection patterns ("robotic language") to make content sound more natural. Unlimited on all paid plans. This addresses a practical concern for publishers: AI-detection tools are increasingly used by content platforms and search engines. The actual effectiveness of the humanizer would require hands-on testing against multiple detection tools to evaluate.</p>

      <h4>Brand Voice Customisation</h4>
      <p>Users can train the AI on their writing style. The Starter plan includes 1 brand voice, Professional includes 5, and Pro Plus 2 includes 25. This enables agencies to maintain distinct brand voices across multiple clients from a single account.</p>

      <h4>Multilingual Content</h4>
      <p>Content generation in 48 languages with local SEO optimisation. The company claims 100+ content languages for the UI localisation system. Quality consistency across languages is an open question — multilingual AI content generation often produces weaker results in lower-resource languages compared to English.</p>

      <h3>Areas Requiring Hands-On Validation</h3>
      <p>Several important performance characteristics cannot be assessed from documentation alone. These include: article quality compared to manual writing on the same keyword, actual SERP ranking effectiveness of generated content, uniqueness and coherence of bulk-generated articles, WordPress MCP reliability across different hosting configurations, effectiveness of the AI humanizer against detection tools, brand voice fidelity beyond surface-level keyword substitution, AI image quality, multilingual accuracy across all 48 languages, customer support responsiveness for a 2-10 person company, and overall platform stability. These are noted as open questions from the research and would benefit from real product testing.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="ux">
      <h2>User Experience</h2>
      <h3>Setup Process</h3>
      <p>The platform is accessed through a web dashboard at seowriting.ai. Users sign up with an email address, receive 3 free article credits (no credit card required), and can begin generating content immediately. The workflow is: select a content type, enter a keyword, adjust optional settings (language, tone, word count, image generation), and click generate. For WordPress users, connecting the site via the MCP server enables auto-publishing.</p>

      <h3>Daily Usage</h3>
      <p>Ongoing activity centers on keyword entry, content generation, reviewing and editing articles in the built-in editor, checking content scores, and publishing to connected WordPress sites. The bulk generation feature allows creating content calendars in single sessions rather than article-by-article workflows.</p>

      <h3>Learning Curve</h3>
      <p>Independent reviewers (AI Gear Base) note a "steep learning curve for beginners" as a limitation. The platform offers multiple content types (blog posts, product roundups, reviews), each with its own configuration options and settings. Users familiar with AI writing tools should find the interface approachable, but complete beginners may need time to understand the different tools, scoring system, and publishing workflow.</p>

      <h3>Interface &amp; Usability</h3>
      <p>We did not get hands-on access to the dashboard, so interface usability is assessed from documentation and third-party descriptions. The public website presents a straightforward feature-by-feature layout. The pricing page is clear and well-structured, which may carry into the product interface. Documents are managed in a list view described as Google-Docs-like, with create, edit, search, and delete operations.</p>
